Django rest framework - edureka
-------------------------------

agenda:
	What is an API?
	Introduction to REST Framework
	What is Rest API?
	Dedo - create a RESTful API

Api provides an interface for the interactivity of multiple softwares (programes)

REST Framework describes the architecture which stands for REpresentational State
 Transfer. It is used for data communication. It uses HTTP to make calls between
 endpoints (machines).
Some methods such as GET, POST, PUT, DELETE.

Any REST Service which use the REST Framework is called a REST API. The return JSON

do `pip install djangorestframework` to install djangorestframework

then the add `rest_framework` to your apps in django

start a project and add it to the apps
start an app

